parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the rear seat belt assembly can lead to failure of the seat belt, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Corrosion of the rear seat belt assembly
failure of the seat belt to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the driver's side seatbelt can lead to failure to restrain the driver in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Driver's side seatbelt does not catch
failure of the seatbelt to lock

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the automatic seat belt can lead to failure to restrain the driver or passenger in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Automatic seat belt does not lock
failure of the seatbelt to stay in place during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the seat belt to retract properly can lead to excessive slack in the belt, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Driver's seat belt fails to retract
leaving too much slack in the belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Corrosion and Fuel Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the fuel tank and fuel lines can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: rust and corrosion on the fuel tank and lines

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective fuel injectors can cause fuel leaks, engine misfires, and poor engine performance, which can lead to accidents, stalling, and decreased fuel efficiency.
symptoms: replacement of fuel injectors multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked or faulty exhaust manifolds can cause carbon monoxide poisoning, decreased engine performance, and increased emissions, posing a risk to vehicle occupants and the environment.
Failure to properly address recall issues related to the fuel system can lead to continued fuel leaks, fires, and accidents, putting vehicle occupants and other road users at risk.
symptoms: corrosion on fuel tank and lines
refusal of dealer to fix recall issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause engine performance issues, loss of power, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
Engine fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the emission vapor canister can cause strong gasoline fumes to enter the passenger compartment, leading to nausea and discomfort.
Engine performance issues can cause slow acceleration, loss of power, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
A camshaft seal leak can cause engine oil leaks, leading to engine damage or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Timing Belt and Water Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt and water pump can cause engine damage or failure, leading to costly repairs.
